{
  "texts": [
    "However, the visualization shapes vary across the different models.",
    "For a soil moisture prediction regression task, we discover that the sample points can be arranged vertically from light to dark in color in t-SNE visualizations of models with great forecasting capacity, such as the Fig. 15h.",
    "Additionally, these visualizations enable us to discern the impact of the attention mechanism and adversarial training on LSTM in Fig. 15k-h advanced data processing capabilities but is less beneficial for soil water prediction tasks.",
    "Generally, from the t-SNE visualizations, it can be summarized that different deep learning models capture distinct intrinsic characteristics of input data and encode them into various vectors for making predictions.",
    "To gain a more comprehensive understanding of their differences, further research is warranted in the future."
  ]
}